## Code Simplification Report

### Changes Made

#### 1. Remove obvious "Save X if changed" comments from `handleSave`
**File**: `frontend/src/components/SettingsPanel.tsx:148-168`
**Type**: Removed redundant comments
**Before**:
```tsx
// Save model settings (these go to per-user DB when auth is active)
if (hasModelChanges) { ... }

// Save API key if changed
if (hasApiKeyChange) { ... }

// Save stale threshold if changed
if (hasStaleThresholdChange) { ... }

// Save compression threshold if changed
if (hasCompressionThresholdChange) { ... }
```
**After**:
```tsx
if (hasModelChanges) { ... }
if (hasApiKeyChange) { ... }
if (hasStaleThresholdChange) { ... }
if (hasCompressionThresholdChange) { ... }
```

The `has*Change` boolean names already say everything the comments said. The new `// Save compression threshold if changed` comment added in this PR followed the same pattern as the pre-existing ones — removing all four is consistent and improves signal-to-noise.

